sentences: Punky Meadows (born Edwin Lionel Meadows, Jr. on February 6, 1950) is an American guitarist known for his glam image as a member of the band Angel.
The Cherry People formed in Southeast Washington, D.C., during the British Invasion of 1964 and changed their name from the Intruders to the English Setters to the Cherry People.

From 1964 to 1972 the band revolved around founding members Chris Grimes (born July 17, 1948), Doug Grimes (born April 24, 1951), and Punky Meadows (born February 6, 1950), with a number of personnel changes taking place from 1972 until the band's demise in June 1975.

In 1964 these four youngsters formed their first band, the Intruders.
In 1967, the English Setters changed their sound and changed their name to the Cherry People, and were later signed to a record deal by Heritage Records.
They toured briefly in 1968, appearing at Caesars Palace and on American Bandstand.
Angel released studio albums from 1975 to 1979 and the live album Live Without a Net in 1980, and disbanded not long thereafter after not achieving mass critical or popular success, except in Japan.

Meadows had retired from the music business, and for 13 years owned and ran a tanning salon in Oakton, Virginia.
In 2015 Punky Meadows made an announcement that he will be coming out of retirement and will be releasing a new solo album on Mainman records.
